# Theming Rules for EduTime Native

## üö´ Never Do This
```typescript
// ‚ùå Hardcoded colors
<Text style={{ color: '#000000' }}>Text</Text>
<View style={{ backgroundColor: 'white' }}>Content</View>

// ‚ùå Single theme only
<Text style={{ color: 'black' }}>Always black</Text>

// ‚ùå Inconsistent color usage
<Text style={{ color: '#11181C' }}>Text</Text>  // Light theme color
<Text style={{ color: '#ECEDEE' }}>Text</Text> // Dark theme color
```

## ‚úÖ Always Do This
```typescript
// ‚úÖ Use themed components
import { ThemedText, ThemedView } from '@/components/ThemedText';
import { useColorScheme } from '@/hooks/useColorScheme';
import { Colors } from '@/constants/Colors';

// For themed components
<ThemedText>Automatically themed text</ThemedText>
<ThemedView>Automatically themed view</ThemedView>

// For custom styling
const colorScheme = useColorScheme();
const theme = Colors[colorScheme ?? 'light'];

<Text style={{ color: theme.text }}>Themed text</Text>
<View style={{ backgroundColor: theme.background }}>Themed view</View>
```

